\v 10 After Iyyov had prayedВҰ243038 for his friends, YahwehВҰ243042 \add вүҲchanged his situation\add* andВҰ243031 \add вүҲgaveВҰ243041\add* \add *him\add* doubleВҰ243049 \add what he had before\add*.\x + \xo 42:10: \xt Yob 1:1-3.\x*
\v 11 Then all of his brothersВҰ243055 and sistersВҰ243058 and everyoneВҰ243084 who'd knownВҰ243062 him beforeВҰ243063, cameВҰ243051 to his houseВҰ243067 and \add вүҲhad a meal\add* withВҰ243067 him, and they comfortedВҰ243070 him and consoled him about all the troublesВҰ243075 thatВҰ243076 YahwehВҰ243079 had broughtВҰ243078 onВҰ243067 him. Then they each gaveВҰ243081 him a \add вүҲsilver coin\add* and a goldВҰ243089 ring.
\p
\v 12 Then YahwehВҰ243093 blessedВҰ243094 the second part of Iyyov's \add life\add* more than the first, and he \add ended up with\add* 14,000 sheepВҰ243106, 6,000 camelsВҰ243109, 1,000 \add working\add* pairs of cows, and 1,000 femaleВҰ243115 donkeysВҰ243115.
\v 13 He \add also\add* had sevenВҰ243120 \add more\add* sonsВҰ243121 andВҰ243122 threeВҰ243122 \add more\add* daughtersВҰ243123
\v 14 who he named YemimahВҰ243129, KetsiahВҰ243132, andВҰ243125 KerenВҰ243135-HappukВҰ243136.
\v 15 No one in the whole country was as beautifulВҰ243141 as Iyyov's daughtersВҰ243142, andВҰ243138 as well as their brothersВҰ243152, their fatherВҰ243149 gaveВҰ243147 them \add each a piece of land\add* as an inheritanceВҰ243150.
\v 16 IyyovВҰ243156 livedВҰ243155 another 140 years afterВҰ243157 \add all\add* that, and was \add even\add* able to see his great-grandchildren.
\v 17 ThenВҰ243175 IyyovВҰ243176 diedВҰ243175 \add вүҲin good circumstances\add* andВҰ243178 at a very old age.
